This paper deals with the problem of discovering latent concepts/relations and predicting missing values in multi-dimensional data, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining. The proposed method, P-Tucker, is a scalable Tucker factorization algorithm for sparse tensors, which is a popular approach for modeling multi-dimensional data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are also relevant to the problem of analyzing and processing large-scale data. Additionally, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are possible categories, as they are related to the storage and manipulation of data and the development of intelligent systems, respectively.
